Q. Favourite thing about the space? 
A. The Space genuinely supports new talent - we take risks right alongside artists and create brilliant new work. Saying yes when other venues might hesitate

Q. Describe your lockdown in 1 word A. Discombobulated

Q. What are you going to take from this lockdown experience? 
A. Like many, Lockdown has been a massive period of change for me. I feel I’ve slipped my moorings and been set adrift. There’s a sense of trepidation, but also great opportunity to it all. Que Sera Sera

Q. Space highlight pre lockdown 
A. Too many to choose from, but seeing audience after audience emotionally broken by ‘that’ scene in  Rachael Claye’s (@NEBCR) Little Women (2018) was incredibly affecting. Oh Lord, the tears!

Q. Space highlight during lockdown 
A. Too many already again, but being able to commission 8 playwrights for 2.0 Fest at a time when opportunities were falling away elsewhere felt important

Q. Lockdown shout out. 
A. Shout out.. to my workshop partner in crime @SaffronMyers for embracing new ways of working and never wavering in her love for new plays and playwrights
